display:flex - All the child element in sigle line
====================
Display Types
1. Inline - Occupies the only th width required for the content and avoids taking of height property
2. Inline block - Occupies the only th width required for the content and it will take height and width
3. block - occupy whole row of the screen

display:flex property will affect to the child elements


D/f b/w Margin and padding
============================
padding - will apply inside the container
margin - around the element
justify content
align items

create layout with flex property